  "texts": [
    "The loss function used is Binary Cross-Entropy Loss (BCELoss), which is defined as:𝐿 = - 1 𝑁 ∑(𝐺 𝑖 • log (𝑃 𝑖) + (1 -𝐺 𝑖) • log (1 -𝑃 𝑖))) 𝑁 𝑖=1(2)Here, 𝐿 represents the overall loss for a batch of tokens, 𝑁is the total number of tokens in the batch, 𝐺 𝑖 is the ground truth score for token 𝑖 and 𝑃 𝑖 is the predicted score for the same token.",
    "Loss guides the model during training to minimize the discrepancies between predicted and ground truth scores, facilitating the accurate assessment of semantic similarity between patent document phrases.",
    "C. DatasetsThe dataset provided for this task consists of pairs of phrases, which include an anchor phrase and a target phrase.",
    "The primary objective is to evaluate the degree of similarity between these phrases, utilizing a rating scale that ranges from 0 (indicating no similarity) to 1 (representing identical meaning).",
    "This assessment of similarity is unique in that it is conducted within the context of patent subject classification, specifically based on the Cooperative Patent Scores in the dataset range from 0 to 1, with increments of 0.25, each representing a specific level of similarity."
